{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_vrtx_01Ckgw839JYjYzczshfmBvs9","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"I have all the context I need. Here's the complete implementation:\n\n## Implementation\n\n### 1. New file: `config/monitoring/prometheus-rules.yaml`\n\n```yaml\napiVersion: monitoring.coreos.com/v1\nkind: PrometheusRule\nmetadata:\n  labels:\n    control-plane: controller-manager\n    app.kubernetes.io/name: prometheusrule\n    app.kubernetes.io/instance: multiarch-tuning-operator\n    app.kubernetes.io/component: monitoring\n    app.kubernetes.io/created-by: multiarch-tuning-operator\n    app.kubernetes.io/part-of: multiarch-tuning-operator\n    app.kubernetes.io/managed-by: kustomize\n  name: image-inspection-alerts\n  namespace: system\nspec:\n  groups:\n    - name: multiarch-tuning-operator.rules\n      rules:\n        - alert: MultiarchImageInspectionFailureRateCritical\n          expr: |\n            (\n              rate(mto_ppo_ctrl_failed_image_inspection_total[5m])\n              /\n              rate(mto_ppo_ctrl_processed_pods_total[5m])\n            ) > 0.05\n          for: 5m\n          labels:\n            severity: critical\n          annotations:\n            message: >-\n              The image inspection failure rate has exceeded 5% over the last 5 minutes.\n              Current failure rate is {{ $value | humanizePercentage }}.\n              This may indicate issues with image registry connectivity or authentication.\n```\n\n### 2. New file: `config/monitoring/kustomization.yaml`\n\n```yaml\nresources:\n- prometheus-rules.yaml\n```\n\n### 3. Modify: `config/default/kustomization.yaml`\n\nAdd `../monitoring` to the `resources` list. The change is to add the line `- ../monitoring` after `- ../webhook`:\n\n```yaml\nresources:\n- ../crd\n- ../rbac\n- ../manager\n- ../webhook\n- ../monitoring\n```\n\n### Key design decisions\n\n- **Metrics used**: The two existing counters from `internal/controller/podplacement/metrics/controller.go`:\n  - `mto_ppo_ctrl_failed_image_inspection_total` — total failed image inspections\n  - `mto_ppo_ctrl_processed_pods_total` — total pods processed by the controller\n- **Expression**: `rate(failures[5m]) / rate(processed[5m]) > 0.05` — fires when more than 5% of processed pods have inspection failures over a 5-minute window. The `rate()` function handles counter resets and gives a per-second rate; dividing gives the failure ratio.\n- **`for: 5m`**: The alert must be continuously firing for 5 minutes before it transitions to `firing` state, preventing transient spikes from paging.\n- **Labels/metadata**: Follow the same labeling conventions as the existing `config/prometheus/monitor.yaml` ServiceMonitor.\n- **Namespace `system`**: Uses `system` which gets rewritten by kustomize's `namespace` field to `openshift-multiarch-tuning-operator`, matching the existing convention.\n\n### Commands to run\n\nNo special make targets are needed — the YAML is purely declarative. To verify kustomize processes it:\n\n```bash\n# Verify the kustomization builds correctly\ncd config/monitoring && kustomize build .\n\n# Verify the full default overlay includes it\ncd config/default && kustomize build .\n```\n\nIf deploying via OLM and the monitoring resources should be part of the bundle, also add `- ../monitoring` to `config/manifests/kustomization.yaml`'s resources list (after `- ../default`, which would already include it transitively)."}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":648,"cache_read_input_tokens":40866,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":648,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":1},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"fef3d052-ba44-4acb-943e-d5a78d326058","uuid":"cdfad4e8-0f7d-442e-ba9b-708b793116b8","timestamp":"2026-07-16T13:46:24.397Z","request_id":"req_vrtx_011Cd5qbNjC2AKNzqpJb2ESw"}
